questions.questionText: Which of the following function of Array object reverses the order of the elements of an array?
Which of the following function of Array object calls a function for each element in the array?
Which of the following function of String object returns the index within the calling String object of the first occurrence of the specified value?
Which of the following function of Boolean object returns a string containing the source of the Boolean object?
Which of the following is true about cookie handling in JavaScript?

answers.answerText: JavaScript can manipulate cookies using the cookie property of the Document object.
JavaScript can read, create, modify, and delete the cookie or cookies that apply to the current web page.
